	Our wives, friends, and children!
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	On February 1, 2003 tragedy struck the Columbia Space Shuttle mission STS-107. The Freelancer Team would like to express their condolences to the seven astronauts who lost their lives. Rick Husband, William McCool, Michael Anderson, Kalpana Chawla, David Brown, Laurel Clark, and Ilan Ramon. Additionally, we would like to express our appreciation to all the brave pioneers of the worldwide space program who have inspired us all by living their dream.

